---
// Placeholder hero — full design/content pass is an open outline task (n_0FNDP5SBW1).
// The CTA copies a setup prompt the visitor pastes into their coding agent; keep the
// commands in it aligned with the CLI and the skills.sh install flow.
const agentInstructions = `Set up Kalamu (repo-local task outliner — https://kalamu.dev) in this repository:

1. Run: npx kalamu init --tour
   It creates .kalamu/ and seeds a self-guided onboarding outline for me, the human.
   Every tour item is marked self — it is a demo for me, never work for you. Do not
   act on, complete, or delete any of it.
   init prints suggested .gitignore entries — add them to .gitignore.
2. Install the Kalamu agent skill so coding agents in this repo know how to use it.
   Detect which agents are in use here (config dirs like .claude/, .cursor/, .agents/, .windsurf/), then run:
   npx skills add hemalr/kalamu -y
   with -a <agent> flags for the agents in use (e.g. -a claude-code). Ask me if you can't tell which agents I use.
3. Verify: npx kalamu validate, then npx kalamu next
   (next exiting with code 2 is expected — the tour tasks are all mine, so there is no agent work yet.)
4. Commit .kalamu/ and the installed skill files.
5. Finally, run npx kalamu open in the background and leave it running — it serves on
   127.0.0.1 and opens my browser on the tour outline.

Then explain to me how to use Kalamu:
- The tour in my browser walks the UI: Enter/Tab/Shift+Tab to outline, Cmd/Ctrl+K for the command palette, ? for the keyboard cheat sheet. Typing p1–p5 in a task sets priority, #words become tags, @me keeps a task for myself so agents skip it.
- Todos I write become tasks agents can execute: they pick up work with kalamu next and mark it done with kalamu done.`;
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>Kalamu — repo-local task outliner for you and your agents</title>
		<meta
			name="description"
			content="A keyboard-first outliner that lives in your repository. Brainstorm in a fast web UI; your coding agents pick up the same tasks through a CLI built for them."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<main>
			<h1>kalamu</h1>
			<p class="tagline">
				A repo-local, keyboard-first outliner for turning developer thoughts into agent-ready tasks.
			</p>

			<button id="copy-cta" data-instructions={agentInstructions}>Copy instructions for your agent</button>
			<p class="cta-hint">Paste into Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, or any coding agent — it sets your repo up and shows you how to use it.</p>

			<details>
				<summary>What gets copied</summary>
				<pre>{agentInstructions}</pre>
			</details>

			<ul>
				<li>One diffable file in your repo — no cloud, no account, no daemon.</li>
				<li>Keyboard-first web UI: outline at the speed of thought, ⌘K for everything else.</li>
				<li>Agents get their own door: <code>kalamu next</code> hands them the most urgent task with full context.</li>
			</ul>
		</main>

		<script>
			const button = document.getElementById('copy-cta') as HTMLButtonElement;
			const original = button.textContent;
			let timer: ReturnType<typeof setTimeout> | undefined;
			button.addEventListener('click', async () => {
				try {
					await navigator.clipboard.writeText(button.dataset.instructions ?? '');
					button.textContent = 'Copied — paste it to your agent';
				} catch {
					button.textContent = 'Copy failed — expand "What gets copied" below';
				}
				clearTimeout(timer);
				timer = setTimeout(() => (button.textContent = original), 2500);
			});
		</script>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	:root {
		color-scheme: light dark;
	}
	body {
		margin: 0;
		min-height: 100vh;
		display: grid;
		place-items: center;
		font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	main {
		max-width: 42rem;
		padding: 2rem;
	}
	h1 {
		font-size: 2.5rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.tagline {
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		opacity: 0.8;
	}
	#copy-cta {
		font: inherit;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
		border-radius: 8px;
		border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 30%, transparent);
		background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 10%, transparent);
		color: inherit;
		cursor: pointer;
	}
	#copy-cta:hover {
		background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 16%, transparent);
	}
	.cta-hint {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		opacity: 0.65;
	}
	details {
		margin: 1rem 0;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
	}
	details pre {
		white-space: pre-wrap;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-radius: 8px;
		border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 20%, transparent);
		overflow-x: auto;
	}
	summary {
		cursor: pointer;
		opacity: 0.7;
	}
	ul {
		padding-left: 1.2rem;
	}
	li + li {
		margin-top: 0.4rem;
	}
</style>
